ww.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/1977-05-07/ |archivedate= 15 March 2013 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|21\n|-\n!Chart (2012)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|134|artist=Deep Purple|song=Smoke On The Water}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1973)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Rank\n|-\n|Canada <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.100214&URLjpg=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/obj/028020/f4/nlc008388.100214.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.100214|title=Image : RPM Weekly|first=Library and Archives|last=Canada|date=December 26, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|34\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>[http://www.musicoutfitters.com/topsongs/1973.htm Musicoutfitters.com]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|50\n|-\n|US ''Cash Box'' <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/70s_files/1973YESP.html |title=Cash Box Year-End Charts: Top 100 Pop Singles, December 29, 1973 |access-date=5 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715135835/http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/70s_files/1973YESP.html |archive-date=15 July 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|52\n|-\n|}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|title=Smoke on the Water|artist=Deep Purple| type = single|relyear=1972|region=United States|award=Gold|certyear=1973}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Italy|artist=Deep Purple|title=Smoke on the Water|type=single|award=Gold|relyear=1972|certyear=2019|accessdate=March 11, 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=Deep Purple|title=Smoke on the Water|award=Silver|certyear=2019|salesamount=200,000|accessdate=February 1, 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true|noshipments=true|streaming=true}}\n\n==Alternative versions==\n{{unreferenced section|date=August 2019}}\n* The 1997 Roger Glover Remix version which appears on the 25th Anniversary Edition reissue of ''[[Machine Head (album)|Machine Head]]'' features a version of the song with an alternate Blackmore guitar solo recorded at the time, and includes Ian Gillan uttering the phrase \"Break a leg, Frank\", among other comments. This is a reference to injuries that Frank Zappa had sustained as a result of being attacked onstage by an audience member at a concert in London, six days after the Montreux fire. A broken leg was among those injuries.\n* The version that appears on ''[[Deep Purple in Concert]]'' also includes Gillan's \"Break a leg\" comment.\n\n==Personnel==\n* [[Ritchie Blackmore]]&nbsp;\u2013 guitars \n* [[Ian Gillan]]&nbsp;\u2013 lead vocals\n* [[Roger Glover]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n* [[Jon Lord]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Hammond organ]]\n* [[Ian Paice]]&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n\n==Rock Aid Armenia version==\n{{unreferenced section|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Smoke on the Water\n| cover      = Smoke-on-the-water-armenia.jpg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Cover for the \"Rock Aid Armenia\" charity release\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Rock Aid Armenia]]\n| album      =\n| released   = 1989\n| format     = [[Gramophone record|7- & 12-inch records]]\n| recorded   = 8\u201315 July 1989\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| writer     =\n*[[Ritchie Blackmore]]\n*[[Ian Gillan]]\n*[[Roger Glover]]\n*[[Jon Lord]]\n*[[Ian Paice]]\n| producer   =\n*[[Gary Langan]]\n*[[Geoff Downes]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|1tsw3nKDlBE|\"Smoke on the Water\" (Rock Aid Armenia)}} }}\n{{Extra album cover\n | header  = 1990 reissue cover\n | type    = single\n | cover   = Smoke-on-the-water-armenia-reissue.jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = Cover of the 7\" reissue of the Rock Aid Armenia single\n}}\n}}\n[[Rock Aid Armenia]], a charity project to help victims of [[1988 Armenian earthquake]] made a charity re-recording of Deep Purple's \"Smoke on the Water\", with different vocalists singing various verses. The single made it to the [[UK Singles Chart|UK Top 40 Singles Chart]].\n\nThe track was recorded by an elite group of contemporary [[prog rock]], [[hard rock]] and [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] musicians who gathered at the historic [[Metropolis Studios]] in [[Chiswick]], [[London]]. Recording began on 8 July 1989 and was completed over 5 different sessions.\n\nThe rock musicians involved in the recording included [[Bryan Adams]], [[Ritchie Blackmore]], [[Bruce Dickinson]], [[Geoff Downes]], [[Keith Emerson]], [[Ian Gillan]], [[David Gilmour]], [[Tony Iommi]], [[Alex Lifeson]], [[Brian May]], [[Paul Rodgers]], [[Chris Squire]] and [[Roger Meddows-Taylor|Roger Taylor]]. [[John Paul Jones (musician)|John Paul Jones]] and [[Jon Lord]] were credited as \"helping\" behind the scenes with the track. The track's producers were [[Gary Langan]] and [[Geoff Downes]]. Talent co-ordination for the record was overseen by Jon Dee, with David Gilmour being the first to join up after a call from Dee. Ian Gillan's manager Phil Banfield also helped out with talent recruitment.\n\n==In world records==\nIn 1994, in [[Vancouver]], British Columbia, Canada, 1,322 guitarists gathered to play the world-famous riff all at the same time for a place in the ''[[Guinness Book of World Records]]''.<ref name=\"Spread Firefox, Crazy Records\">{{cite web|url=http://www.spreadfirefox.com/en-US/worldrecord/webrecords|title=Spread Firefox, Crazy Records|website=spreadfirefox.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080530232442/http://www.spreadfirefox.com/en-US/worldrecord/webrecords|archivedate=30 May 2008|df=dmy-all|access-date=29 May 2008}}</ref> On Sunday 3 June 2007, in [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]] this record was topped with 1,721 guitarists.<ref name=\"Spread Firefox, Crazy Records\"/> Just 20 days later, in the German city of [[Leinfelden-Echterdingen]] by the group 'Party Blues In Bb' with over 1,800 other people involved.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gitarrenweltrekord.de/?geschichte |title=Die Geschichte des Gitarrenweltrekords |accessdate=11 March 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719032246/http://www.gitarrenweltrekord.de/?geschichte |archivedate=19 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> \nThe record was again topped on 1 May 2009, in [[Wroc\u0142aw]], Poland, when 6,346 guitar players, joined by current Deep Purple guitarist [[Steve Morse]], performed the song during the Thanks Jimi Festival.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.stevemorse.com/tour_blog.html |title=Official Steve Morse Blog |accessdate=4 May 2009 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090430021436/http://www.stevemorse.com/tour_blog.html |archivedate=30 April 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cichonski.art.pl/eng/record.htm|title=\"Thanks Jimi Festival\" 2009 and Guitar Guinness Record|accessdate=4 May 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090422152803/http://cichonski.art.pl/eng/record.htm|archivedate=22 April 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book|author=[[Ian Christe|Christe, Ian]]|date=2003|title=Sound of the Beast: The Complete Headbanging History of Heavy Metal|publisher=HarperCollins|isbn=0-380-81127-8|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/soundofbeastcomp0000chri}}\n* {{cite web|url= http://www.deep-purple.net/features/smoke/smoke-on-the-water.html |title=Smoke On The Water - the story|website= Deep-Purple.net}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|deep-purple|smoke-on-the-water}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Deep Purple}}\n\n[[Category:Deep Purple songs]]\n[[Category:1972 songs]]\n[[Category:1973 singles]]\n[[Category:Frank Zappa]]\n[[Category:Songs about Switzerland]]